# sectorcalc.com — Permanent Architecture Law

## A — PURE ENGLISH ONLY

The entire code structure, infrastructure, visible and invisible architecture, components, comments, UI strings, docs-in-repo, configs, and schemas for **sectorcalc.com** MUST always be coded in **pure English**.

Non-English content is **NEVER** allowed and must **NEVER** be used inside any file.

Verification: `node scripts/check-language.mjs --strict`

## B — STEEL STRUCTURE (must not break)

1. Firebase Hosting
2. JSON infrastructure
3. Paddle payment system
4. Million-USD-grade infrastructure
5. Irreversible setup (no casual rewrites of foundations)

### Paddle research (locked)

- Paddle = Merchant of Record (MoR) — carries global tax liability
- Fee: 5% + $0.50 flat (tax, fraud, chargebacks included)
- Automatic tax compliance in 200+ countries
- Webhook-based integration
- Optimized for SaaS and digital products

### Firebase Hosting

- Static hosting, CDN, free SSL
- Free tier: 10GB storage, 10GB/month bandwidth
- Custom domain, atomic deploys
- Cloud Functions integration (optional)

### Cursor IDE (workflow)

- AI-assisted code editor (VS Code-based) — for development only
- Ideal for large codebase management
- Codebase indexing, AI chat, code generation
- Git integration

### JSON infrastructure

- Every calculation tool is defined via JSON Schema
- Reference data lives in JSON files
- Form schemas are JSON
- Versioned and immutable

### Combined stack

- Firebase Hosting (static + CDN)
- JSON-based architecture (no backend required for core calc)
- Cursor IDE (development workflow)
- Paddle (payments + MoR + global tax)
- Deterministic calculation engine (client-side)
- Immutable version control (Git + JSON Schema validation)

### Million-USD-grade infrastructure targets

- Scalability: Firebase CDN global; Paddle global MoR
- Reliability: 99.99% uptime target; deterministic engine
- Security: SOC 2 path; client-side data; Paddle PCI compliance
- Maintainability: JSON Schema, versioned, testable
- Extensibility: new tools = new JSON files

### Irreversible setup

- Git repo structure
- CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions + Firebase deploy)
- JSON Schema validation (pre-commit hooks)
- Test suite (deterministic verification; Vitest in current pin)
- Paddle webhook handlers (idempotent)
- Data store (Firebase Firestore and/or local IndexedDB)

## C — NO AI SMELL (hard ban list)

Forbidden in product marketing / UI / copy:

- "AI-Powered"
- "Machine Learning"
- "Generative"
- Chatbot
- Stock photography
- "Neural", "Transformer", "LLM"

Use instead:

- "Built by engineers who still get their hands dirty"
- "We tested this on 47 shop floors before shipping"
- "Deterministic Engine: Same inputs always produce identical outputs"

### Human-engineer feel

| Element | Application |
|---------|-------------|
| Fonts | JetBrains Mono (formulas), Inter (headings), Caveat (handwritten notes) |
| Icons | Hand-drawn SVG (imperfect lines) |
| Photos | Real workshop shots from a phone |
| Signatures | Real engineer LinkedIn profiles |
| Micro-copy | "Checks out" (not "done"); "Heads up" (not "warning") |

## D — TRUST IN 5 SECONDS

### Above-the-fold trust stack

- SOC 2 Type II badge (clickable verification)
- "No data leaves your device" (client-side proof)
- "4.9/5 on G2 (247 reviews)"
- Real customer photo + LinkedIn link

### 5-second test

| Question | Answer |
|----------|--------|
| What does it do? | "Engineering calculators that catch costly mistakes" |
| Who is it for? | "Shop floor engineers, estimators, QA managers" |
| Is it trustworthy? | "SOC 2 certified, deterministic engine, 2,400+ engineers" |
| How much? | "Free to start, Pro at $99/year" |
| What should I do? | "Run My First Calculation — Free, No Signup" |
